# Landing Hero Rework — Isometric Lissajous SVG

## Overview

Replace the current landing page hero (WebM video + poster image, integrations showcase, benefits grid) with a minimal isometric Lissajous SVG in a `bg-accent rounded-md` 16:9 container. The page signals too much product maturity — strip it back to the essentials while we figure out what Lightfast really is.

## Current State Analysis

The landing page at `apps/www/src/app/(app)/(marketing)/(landing)/page.tsx` currently has:
- **Hero section** — WebM video (desktop) + static poster image (mobile), absolutely positioned behind text
- **IntegrationShowcase section** — provider grid
- **Connect Your Tools section** — 6 benefit cards with icons
- **FAQ section** — accordion
- **Changelog Preview** — recent entries
- **WaitlistCTA** — bottom CTA

The isometric box + Lissajous visual already exists in `packages/app-remotion/src/compositions/blog-why-we-built-featured/blog-why-we-built-featured.tsx`, but it depends on:
- `@repo/ui/lib/brand/lissajous.ts` — pure math, already in a shared package
- `packages/app-remotion/src/compositions/landing-hero/shared/iso/` — pure math (project, createBox, facePath, shapeBounds), but trapped inside app-remotion

### Key Discoveries:

- The iso utilities (`math.ts`, `shape.ts`, `types.ts`) have **zero Remotion dependencies** — they're pure geometry functions
- Only 2 files in app-remotion consume the iso utilities: `blog-why-we-built-featured.tsx` and `landing-hero/sections/logo-animation.tsx`
- The Lissajous curve is already shared via `@repo/ui/lib/brand`
- The blog composition uses golden-ratio framing at `PHI_INV_SQ ≈ 0.382` from top-left — we need this mirrored to the right (`1 - PHI_INV_SQ ≈ 0.618` from left)

## Desired End State

The landing page hero shows:
1. **Left side**: "Building the superintelligence layer for founders" text + Early Access CTA (unchanged)
2. **Right side**: A `bg-accent rounded-md` 16:9 container holding the isometric box with Lissajous curve, hairlines extending to canvas edges, golden-ratio anchored to the upper-right power point

The IntegrationShowcase and Connect Your Tools sections are gone. FAQ, Changelog Preview, and WaitlistCTA remain.

### Verification:

- `pnpm check && pnpm typecheck` passes
- `pnpm build:www` succeeds (or `pnpm --filter lightfast-www build`)
- Visual inspection: the 16:9 accent container with isometric SVG renders correctly on the right side of the hero
- The Remotion compositions still work (imports updated, no breakage)

## What We're NOT Doing

- Not adding animation to the SVG (static only — matches the blog featured image)
- Not changing the hero text, CTA, or changelog badge
- Not touching FAQ, Changelog Preview, or WaitlistCTA sections
- Not modifying the Remotion compositions themselves (only updating their import paths)
- Not removing the WebM/poster files from `public/images/` (can clean up later)

## Implementation Approach

Extract the iso utilities to `@repo/ui/lib/iso`, create a static SVG component, then rework the landing page in one pass.

---

## Phase 1: Extract Iso Utilities to `@repo/ui/lib/iso`

### Overview

Move the isometric projection math from `packages/app-remotion` to `packages/ui` so it's available to any package without depending on Remotion.

### Changes Required:

#### 1. Create `packages/ui/src/lib/iso/types.ts`

**File**: `packages/ui/src/lib/iso/types.ts`
**Action**: Copy from `packages/app-remotion/src/compositions/landing-hero/shared/iso/types.ts` verbatim.

```ts
/** 2D point [x, y] in screen coordinates (y-down) */
export type Vec2 = [number, number];

/** Ordered list of 2D points forming a closed polygon */
export type Polygon = Vec2[];

/** Visual face orientation for coloring */
export type FaceType = "top" | "front" | "right";

/** A projected 2D face with optional holes (from boolean subtraction) */
export interface Face {
  contour: Polygon;
  holes: Polygon[];
  type: FaceType;
}

/** A renderable shape: ordered collection of faces (back-to-front) */
export interface Shape {
  faces: Face[];
}

/** Axis-aligned 3D box: (x,y) = ground plane, z = vertical */
export interface Box3D {
  d: number;
  h: number;
  w: number;
  x: number;
  y: number;
  z: number;
}

/** 2D bounding rectangle */
export interface Bounds {
  maxX: number;
  maxY: number;
  minX: number;
  minY: number;
}
```

#### 2. Create `packages/ui/src/lib/iso/math.ts`

**File**: `packages/ui/src/lib/iso/math.ts`
**Action**: Copy from `packages/app-remotion/src/compositions/landing-hero/shared/iso/math.ts` verbatim.

